<td><FONT SIZE="1" FACE="Verdana, Arial" COLOR="#2f2f4f">Originally posted by Selenite on 06-01-2002 04:58 PM<BR></FONT>
<TEXTAREA NAME="EditedMessage" ROWS=10 COLS=45 WRAP="VIRTUAL">The problem being described isn't shortage of clerics, though.  It's the inordinate disparity in number of clerics vs. number of any other class (taken singly) that needs to be on a raid.

You don't need 6 to 10 of ANY other class, except clerics, for any raid.  Raids don't get called off 'cause....we don't have enough rangers!  (You can replace 'rangers' with any class here, it's not any one particular class, including Druids, despite the way so many Clerics get so defensive around Druids).

Like someone else already pointed out, each other class needs 1 or 2 at a raid, at *most*.  You need 1 shaman for most raids, but they're not essential if the mob can't be slowed (though the buffs sure help).  But you don't need 8 shamans for any raid.  You need 1 warrior for every raid.  2 or 3 help.  You don't need 8.  See where I'm going?

The problem they want to adress isn't that CH needs to be given to someone else, or that there's not enough clerics.  Indeed, it seems to be kind of the reverse of that - too many clerics, through cleric-demand.  Bot clerics are common because of their necessity for raids to function.  

Like some people have pointed out, though, the best solution?  To redesign (or at least, properly design all *new* mobs) to NOT be a cleric-fest.  To only *require* 2 or 3 clerics at most.  Encounters can easily be designed so that more even numbers of people are required.  Why is it that adding a cleric to a raid helps a lot, but adding a Necromancer, for example, is of limited use (particularly if you don't put them to work doing what?  Oh, yeah, feeding the cleric mana.)

More than 3 mages on a raid is useless (assuming they're supposed to be a pet class, not another infusion of mana for clerics) because no more than 3 pets can attack a single enemy at a time.  Or indeed - more than 3 Mage, Necro, and Beastlord, all put together.  If you have 1 of each, you have no room for any more.

Don't give Druids CH, most of them don't want it anyway, and it wouldn't solve the problem (it'd just shift it to mean you need at least 8 clerics or druids).  Redesign the mobs, however, so that they can provide an adequate challenge, without requiring a string of clerics CHing the main tank.

------------------
Well Met,
Selenite Darkfeather,
Priestess of Innoruuk.</TEXTAREA>
</td></tr>
